    <exercise id="fs-id2020144" type="conceptual-questions"><problem id="fs-id2213747">
<para id="import-auto-id2097381">Measurements of the weak and fluctuating magnetic fields associated with brain activity are called magnetoencephalograms (MEGs). Do the brain’s magnetic fields imply coordinated or uncoordinated nerve impulses? Explain. </para></problem></exercise>
