  </exercise><exercise id="fs-id1467801" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1537634">  <para id="eip-id1168951412604"><title>Integrated Concepts</title></para>  <para id="import-auto-id2554872">(a) What voltage will accelerate electrons to a speed of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>6.00</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>? (b) Find the radius of curvature of the path of a <emphasis effect="italics">proton</emphasis> accelerated through this potential in a 0.500-T field and compare this with the radius of curvature of an electron accelerated through the same potential.</para></problem></exercise><exercise id="fs-id1533546" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1764142">  <para id="eip-id1168951409409"><title>Integrated Concepts</title></para>  <para id="import-auto-id1869627">Find the radius of curvature of the path of a 25.0-MeV proton moving perpendicularly to the 1.20-T field of a cyclotron.</para>
